{
  "doc_id": "58526",
  "text": "Prevention of obesity and insulin resistance includes strategies that need to be started early in life, already during pregnancy and the perinatal period [CITATION_1] . It is important to strongly recommend breast feeding and offer guidance for appropriated food choice, caloric intake and exercise for children [CITATION_2] . The first step of prevention must aim towards maintaining normal BMI [CITATION_3] . A rapid weight gain must be avoided during the first years of life as it causes an early adiposity rebound, which is a well-known risk factor for future persistence of obesity [CITATION_4] . When obesity is already developed, a programme of secondary prevention is required, in order to reverse or at least to avoid progression of obesity and reduce the risk of co-morbidities [CITATION_5] .",
